      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Frederic W. Goudy (1865-1947) was an American printer and type designer of more than 120 
		fonts, among them Copperplate Gothic, Kennerley, and Goudy Old Style.  Frederic's wife Bertha M. Goudy worked 
		closely with him and was a noted graphic designer in her own right.  Both Frederic and Bertha were self-taught.  
		Goudy had a long-standing relationship with Syracuse University (SU); he was awarded the distinguished service 
		medal by SU's Newhouse School of Journalism in 1936, received an honorary doctorate from SU in 1939, and was 
		appointed a lecturer at the School of Journalism in 1940.  Dates given are the dates the typeface was designed, but may not be the actual date this type was cast.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Goudy Type Collection</emph> consists of two large cabinets of lead type, designed 
			by noted American type designer Frederic W. Goudy.    Important fonts in the collection include Deepdene, Sherman, and Goudy Newstyle.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
